etymologies: 1930s: French, ‘rubbing, friction’, from frotter ‘to rub’, of unknown origin

definitions: the technique or process of taking a rubbing from an uneven surface to form the basis of a work of art.
shortDefinitions: technique or process of taking rubbing from uneven surface

definitions: a work of art produced by taking a rubbing from an uneven surface.
shortDefinitions: work of art produced by taking rubbing from uneven surface

definitions: the practice of touching or rubbing against the clothed body of another person in a crowd as a means of obtaining sexual gratification.
shortDefinitions: practice of touching or rubbing against clothed body of another person in crowd
